Imagine a future where every unknown phone call comes with a guarantee of IMMEDIATE financial compensation. \nBy using this app, you are making that future a reality. Thank you.
\n\nWe developed this application to fight back against scammers who steal more than $10 Billion
every year from vulnerable people through phone fraud. We will give you power over your most
precious commodity. Your Time.
\n\nThis app will always be free to use, because everyone that joins us becomes part of the
bigger picture of data revolution. If enough of us refuse to answer calls, the bad actors will notice and you will get paid for your data.
\n\nThank you for being part of the revolution.
\n\nHelp us with brutally honest feedback and bug reports.
\n\nSincerely,
\nAEG, DRJ, VJ, JC, PJG, CR.
Our Commitment
Our mission is to create a market which financially rewards all its participants and is strengthened by numbers. Through KarmaCall, your data becomes a commodity which you have the power to sell or keep to yourself. We believe the future of great businesses is in shared prosperity and that requires that you are financially compensated for your data and time. \n\nWe stand by the new European Union policy, giving our clients and users a greater say in what happens with their data.
What is GDPR?
The GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation) went into effect on May 25, 2018 in the European Union. The GDPR applies to every company that processes EU citizens\' PII (Personally Identifiable Information). This new law prioritizes the importance of the protection and privacy of your personal information in several key areas. The state of California recently passed the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). All the rights of CCPA are met by complying with the GDPR which KarmaCall does, as described below. \n\nFirst, KarmaCall provides the ability to consent to data collection in an easily accessible format. At KarmaCall, we store your personal contact information – phone number, digital wallet, as well as data concerned with our performance of contract which in part captures digital wallet transactions for anti-spam purposes and length of your call times for improving our services. Along with your basic contact information, we use Flurry Analytics to track how you use our application so we can learn how to improve it to make your experience as enjoyable as possible. Any other data which is VOLUNTARILY provided by you (demographics and psychographics), but is not required for our spam-blocking features, will be stored as well. \n\nSecond, KarmaCall supplies the opportunity to request your data. We display the data currently held under your user and/or business entity in a user-friendly format. KarmaCall does not sell or provide your data to any 3rd party sources for any reason. \n\nThird, KarmaCall presents the option to have all data we have collected, deleted on request. If you make this request, we will comply without undue delay except as required by other laws. For example, some financial data may not be deleted if it is required for tax records. \n\nFor more information, an overview of the EU GDPR regulations can be found here.

I have read & understood and accept the terms and conditions of the service, and I allow the service provider to scan my national ID and save it and use it securely for the provided services. Verification of identity: A national ID is a reliable and standardized form of identification that helps banks verify the identity of the account holder.
Compliance with regulations: Banks are required to comply with various regulations, such as anti-money laundering (AML) and know your customer (KYC) rules.
Enhanced security: By requesting a national ID, banks can enhance the security of their customers\' accounts. It helps protect against unauthorized access and ensures that only the account holder can perform transactions.
Prevention of financial crimes: A national ID can help banks in their efforts to prevent financial crimes, such as money laundering, terrorist financing, and tax evasion.
Streamlined processes: Requesting a national ID helps banks streamline their account opening processes. It provides a standardized and easily verifiable form of identification, making it easier for banks to verify customer information and complete the necessary paperwork.
